The program will simply output "Hello, World!" to the console. This will be done using a single class with the primary method. Considering that it's a simple console application, no non-standard dependencies will be required.

1. Class:
    - **HelloWorld** : The class that contains the implementation of the program.

2. Method:
    - **PrintMessage** : This method will be responsible for printing the "Hello, World!" message to the console.

## Specification 

**Class: HelloWorld**
- Description: This class encapsulates the logic to print a "Hello, World!" message to the console.

**Method: void PrintMessage()**
- Description: This method prints the "Hello, World!" message to the console.
- Input: Nothing
- Output: prints "Hello, world!" to the console

The C# environment is so well-equipped that no external libraries or dependencies are required to execute this application. It solely depends on .NET Core SDK which includes all the necessary packages to build and run the console application.